---
import CaseStudy from '../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---
<CaseStudy title="Cansu Tecimer" description="Portfolio of Cansu Tecimer — product designer and UX leader in Berlin.">

  <section class="hero container">
    <h1 class="display">Hi, I'm <em>Cansu</em>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Product designer and UX leader in Berlin. Currently co-founding Steady — an AI cycling coaching app.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="story container">
    <div class="story-grid">
      <aside class="story-label">
        <span class="index">01</span>
        <h2>Selected work</h2>
      </aside>
      <div class="story-body">
        <article class="company-block">
          <h3 class="company-name">
            <img class="company-logo" src="/images/LOGO-Steady.png" alt="" />
            <span>Steady</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="company-blurb">Steady is an AI cycling coaching app for cyclists who have specific goals.</p>
          <p class="company-blurb">I co-founded it with my husband — a cycling enthusiast training for multiple events. We started in January 2026 with an idea and built a fully functioning web app in a few months. Now focusing on reaching more users, learning from the ones we have, and improving the platform.</p>
          <ul class="company-projects">
            <li><a href="/portfolio/steady-app/">Building a cycling coaching app from zero</a></li>
            <li><a href="/portfolio/steady-marketing-site/">Building Steady's marketing site</a></li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="company-block">
          <h3 class="company-name">
            <img class="company-logo" src="/images/LOGO-GYG.png" alt="" />
            <span>GetYourGuide</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="company-blurb">GetYourGuide is a marketplace for travel experiences, helping travelers discover and book everything from iconic attractions to hidden-gem local experiences. While biggest in Europe, they have expanded to 18,000+ cities globally.</p>
          <p class="company-blurb">As Senior UX Manager, I wore many hats as the company evolved (including through COVID). I primarily led UX for the Growth Product Group — audience growth, engagement, and the early discovery experience. I also championed and resourced Compass, GYG's design system.</p>
          <ul class="company-projects">
            <li><a href="/portfolio/homepage-design-for-returning-users/">Homepage design for returning users</a></li>
            <li><a href="/portfolio/vision-for-holistic-discovery-experience/">Vision for a holistic discovery experience</a></li>
            <li><a href="/portfolio/improving-destination-discovery/">Improving destination discovery</a></li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="company-block">
          <h3 class="company-name">
            <img class="company-logo" src="/images/LOGO-HF.png" alt="" />
            <span>HelloFresh</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="company-blurb">HelloFresh started as a meal-kit delivery service but has expanded into many arenas in the food space. Founded in Berlin in 2011, it's the global market leader in meal kits, operating across 18 countries.</p>
          <p class="company-blurb">I joined as the second designer and grew with the company through its IPO. As Head of UX, I scaled the design team from 2 to 14 and built the foundations — ways of working, design system, quality standards, research, and hiring.</p>
          <ul class="company-projects">
            <li><a href="/portfolio/hellofresh-my-menu/">HelloFresh My Menu 2.0</a></li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story container">
    <div class="story-grid">
      <aside class="story-label">
        <span class="index">02</span>
        <h2>Ways to work together</h2>
      </aside>
      <div class="story-body">
        <p class="first-para">I work with teams as an embedded design partner. The founding designer for a team shaping a product, or the senior hire who builds out a design practice for a team past zero-to-one. I fill the design gap, build alongside the team, and hand it off when they're ready to take it on.</p>
        <div class="engagement-grid">
          <article class="engagement-card">
            <p class="engagement-tag">Shaping products</p>
            <h3>Embedded "founding" designer</h3>
            <p class="engagement-who">For founders and small teams shaping a product, I'll be the design and product partner.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Hands-on product thinking and UX, end-to-end when needed</li>
              <li>Research, problem framing, flow design, MVPs</li>
              <li>Close partnership with engineering to ship and learn fast</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="engagement-card">
            <p class="engagement-tag">Shaping teams</p>
            <h3>Fractional design leadership</h3>
            <p class="engagement-who">For teams further along, I take on fractional leadership.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Hands-on design support if needed</li>
              <li>Building the design function (hiring, building processes, etc.)</li>
              <li>Partnering with PM and engineering to define ways of working</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story container">
    <div class="story-grid">
      <aside class="story-label">
        <span class="index">03</span>
        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      </aside>
      <div class="story-body">
        <p class="first-para">I'm always happy to chat — about projects, design, managing design teams, or where our industry is headed.</p>
        <p><a href="mailto:cansutecimer@gmail.com" class="contact-link">cansutecimer@gmail.com</a> · <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/cansu-tecimer-a3458b47/" class="contact-link">LinkedIn</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</CaseStudy>
